\subsection{Competency Analytics}
Beyond per-question adaptation, the dashboard computes a Competency Index (CI) as a weighted average over the ten most recent tests with harmonic weights (1/rank), giving recent performance greater influence. Per-domain accuracy (Aptitude, Reasoning, Verbal) is tracked independently with competency bands: Expert ($\geq$85), Advanced ($\geq$70), Intermediate ($\geq$50), Beginner ($<$50). Three persistence models provide a complete audit trail from individual responses to aggregate competency profiles.

\subsection{Advantages of LLM-Native Adaptation}
Delegating difficulty reasoning to LLM agents offers: (1) natural language maintainability---rules are modified in prompts without rewriting code; (2) contextual nuance---SOLPA interprets ``fast''/``slow'' without hard thresholds; (3) explainability---full reasoning chains support APOT audit goals \cite{outay2024}; (4) zero pre-calibration---deployable without item bank construction \cite{hambleton1985}; (5) dynamic question generation eliminating the traditional bottleneck entirely. The trade-off of LLM non-determinism is mitigated by structured output parsing, ``Medium'' defaults, and the synchronous rule-based fallback layer.

